New email from Zac <notifications@github.com>
Subject: [stonerl/Thaw] perf(image-cache): replace O(n) LRU array with O(1) dictionary-based tracking (PR #162)

 ## Summary

  - Replace `accessOrder: [MenuBarItemTag]` array with `accessTimestamps:
  [MenuBarItemTag: UInt64]` dictionary + monotonic counter
  - Eliminates repeated `removeAll { $0 == tag }` linear scans (O(n) per access) with
  O(1) dictionary lookups
  - Remove the double-reverse deduplication pass — dictionary is inherently
  deduplicated
  - Extract `leastRecentlyUsedTags(count:excluding:)` helper for eviction queries

  ## Motivation

  Every cache read via `updateAccessOrder(for:)` and every bulk update in
  `updateCacheWithoutChecks` performed O(n) linear scans through the `accessOrder`
  array (up to 200 items). With multiple call sites doing `removeAll { $0 == tag }`, a
  single cache update cycle could trigger hundreds of linear scans.

  ## Complexity comparison

  | Operation | Before (Array) | After (Dictionary) |
  |---|---|---|
  | `updateAccessOrder` | O(n) removeAll + O(1) append | O(1) counter increment + dict
  set |
  | Bulk update (n tags) | O(n²) — n × removeAll | O(n) — n × dict set |
  | Cache cleanup | O(n) removeAll per tag | O(1) removeValue per tag |
  | LRU eviction | O(n) filter + prefix | O(n log n) sort (infrequent) |
  | Deduplication pass | O(n) reverse-filter-reverse | Not needed (dict is unique) |

  ## Test plan

  - [ ] Build succeeds with no warnings
  - [ ] Verify IceBar displays menu bar item images correctly
  - [ ] Verify Layout Bar in Settings shows images
  - [ ] Verify search panel shows item images
  - [ ] Monitor console logs for "Cache inconsistency" warnings (should not appear)
